\ destruct ( coll -- v0 v1 ... vN-1 ) — push the elements of a collection
\ onto the data stack. For frames, pushes :key v :key v ... in key order.
\ Accepts array, set, and frame; errors on other types.

\ basic array destruct
[ 10 20 30 ] destruct .s clear cr        \ [ 10 20 30 ]

\ empty array — nothing pushed
[ ] destruct .s clear cr                 \ [ ]

\ single-element array
[ 42 ] destruct . cr                     \ 42

\ mixed types
[ "a" 5 :sym ] destruct .s clear cr      \ [ a 5 :sym ]

\ nested values stay intact (each item pushed as-is)
[ [ 1 2 ] [ 3 4 ] ] destruct .s clear cr \ [ [ 1 2 ] [ 3 4 ] ]

\ set: elements come out in the set's internal (sorted) order
< 3 1 2 > destruct .s clear cr           \ [ 1 2 3 ]

\ empty set
< > destruct .s clear cr                 \ [ ]

\ frame: pushes :key value :key value ... in key-sort order
{ :a 1 :b 2 } destruct .s clear cr       \ [ :a 1 :b 2 ]

\ frame: keys come back as symbols (not raw cells)
{ :x 10 } destruct swap . . cr           \ :x 10

\ empty frame
{ } destruct .s clear cr                 \ [ ]

\ round-trip: destruct an array then rebuild
[ 1 2 3 ] destruct 3 array . cr          \ [ 1 2 3 ]

\ non-collection — error
42 destruct
"hello" destruct
:sym destruct

\ empty stack — underflow
destruct

\ destruct-to ( source target -- )
\ Writes each item of source into the variable named by the corresponding
\ target item. Target items may be symbols (auto-create variable if missing,
\ cache as XT on the way) or XTs (used directly, must reference a variable).
\ Source and target must be arrays of equal length.

\ Basic: auto-create three new variables from symbol targets
[ 1 2 3 ] [ :dta :dtb :dtc ] destruct-to
dta . dtb . dtc . cr                            \ 1 2 3

\ Re-use existing variables
[ 10 20 30 ] [ :dta :dtb :dtc ] destruct-to
dta . dtb . dtc . cr                            \ 10 20 30

\ Caching: re-using the same target array across calls — first call resolves
\ symbols, subsequent calls hit the cached XTs.
variable dt-targets
[ :dtd :dte ] to dt-targets
[ 7 8 ] dt-targets destruct-to                  \ first call resolves
[ 11 12 ] dt-targets destruct-to                \ second call uses cached XTs
dtd . dte . cr                                  \ 11 12

\ Mixed targets: XT (pre-declared) and symbol (auto-create) in same array
variable dtf
[ 100 200 300 ] [ ' dtf :dtg :dth ] destruct-to
dtf . dtg . dth . cr                            \ 100 200 300

\ Mixed value types: any Val tag works on the source side
[ "hi" :sym 42 ] [ :dt-str :dt-sym :dt-num ] destruct-to
dt-str . dt-sym . dt-num . cr                   \ hi :sym 42

\ Length mismatch — error
[ 1 2 ] [ :dtx :dty :dtz ] destruct-to

\ Non-array source — error
42 [ :dtx ] destruct-to

\ Non-array target — error
[ 1 ] 42 destruct-to

\ Bad target item (neither symbol nor xt) — error
[ 1 ] [ 99 ] destruct-to
